
Ranger Help for: trailblaze(blaze)
==================================

SYNTAX:      trailblaze to <target>/backtrack
USAGE:       forest,plains,swamp,desert,jungle,hills,road,beach,
             mountain,arctic,barren,outside
SLOT COST:   8
BASE SP:     65 sp
SKILL TYPE:  aid

SUMMARY:    
Trailblaze allows a Ranger to come to the rescue of a lost explorer.
The explorer must have called for the Rangers help by using the 'helpme'
emote. Once a call has been made, the Ranger only has about 5 minutes,
after which he or she forgets from which direction the call came from.
A Ranger can't trailblaze from just anywhere, they must be fairy close,
approximately within the same realm(wizard's area) and both the Ranger
and the target explorer must be above ground...Rangers can't trailblaze
through dirt and rock. Once there, the Ranger may elect to 'backtrack'
to his or her original location at no extra cost. If the explorer you
trailblazed to is there, they will follow you while you backtrack.

